# Athlete Profile
# Copy this file to athlete.md and fill in your data.
# This file is sent to Claude as context for coaching reports.
# Write in English for best results — Claude will respond in Portuguese.

## Personal Data
- **Age:** 30 | **Height:** 1.75m | **Weight:** 75kg
- **Location:** Your city/country

## Athletic Background
- Describe your sport history, years active, time away from sport
- Any relevant past training experience

## Injury & Health History
- **Known issues:** List any chronic injuries or conditions
- **Current status:** How you feel day to day
- **Sleep:** Hours per night
- **Nutrition:** Any relevant diet info, weight journey
- **Shoes:** Model, condition, surface you run on

## Goals
- Your primary running goal (e.g., run 5km continuously)
- Secondary goals (weight loss, endurance, etc.)

## Coaching Principles (always apply)
1. Target pace range (e.g., 9:30–10:30/km)
2. Target HR zone (e.g., Zone 2: 115–135 bpm)
3. Any safety thresholds (e.g., flag if max HR > 165)
4. Recovery priorities

## Analysis Rules — Read Before Every Report
- Describe how you record activities (e.g., warm-up/cool-down included in recording)
- How to calculate actual running time from Strava data
- Any quirks in your data that the coach should know about
